{
  "text": "The diagnostic performance of bright lumen MRC was assessed in several studies 26 27 using conventional colonoscopy as the standard of reference. While most mass lesions smaller than 5 mm in size were missed, [CITATION_1] almost all lesions exceeding 10 mm were correctly identified (table 1). In a study by Pappalardo et al [CITATION_2] MRC even detected a higher total number of polyps exceeding 10 mm in size than conventional colonoscopy. MRC identified additional polyps in regions of the colon not reached by colonoscopy.",
  "correct_citation": {
